# Sidebar nav icon colors

When adding or changing sidebar items in the main shell:

1. **Always add/update the icon mapping** in `apps/web/src/components/shell/ShellNavIcon.tsx`.
   - Any new `ShellNavIconId` must have:
     - a concrete icon component mapping in `ShellNavIcon()`
     - an explicit color mapping in `tone()`
2. **Do not rely on default color fallback** for new icons.
3. **Use the sidebar palette** (from the colored reference):
   - `#7a7aff` (indigo)
   - `#4fc3f7` (sky)
   - `#f48fb1` (pink)
   - `#f06292` (rose)
   - `#9575cd` (violet)
   - `#4dd0e1` (cyan)
   - `#4db6ac` (teal)
   - `#81c784` (green)
   - `#a5d6a7` (mint)
   - `#ffb74d` (amber)
   - `#ff8a65` (orange)
   - `#a89af7` (lilac)
4. Keep icon stroke style consistent:
   - `h-[18px] w-[18px]`
   - `strokeWidth={1.9}`
   - `absoluteStrokeWidth`
   - rounded line caps/joins

This keeps the sidebar visually consistent whenever nav items are added or renamed.

## Expanded role sub-items (Manager / HR / Admin)

When editing expanded role panels in `AppShell`:

1. Keep grouped sub-items in the HTML reference style:
   - Section labels are uppercase, tight letter-spacing, role-tinted.
   - Sub-items render with a **small colored dot** (5px) instead of a left icon.
   - Active sub-item uses a soft row background + brighter role-tinted text.
   - Section breaks include a subtle divider line before each new group.
2. Keep role palettes consistent across headers + sub-items:
   - Manager: base `#a89af7`, muted text `#7a7a84`, active text `#c4bef8`, section label `#524e6a`
   - HR: base `#4fc3f7`, muted text `#6a7a84`, active text `#9fd8f0`, section label `#1e4a58`
   - Admin: base `#ff8a65`, muted text `#8a7a74`, active text `#ffb09a`, section label `#5a3a2a`
3. For role panel content items, set `section` on nav items (in `adminGates`) so grouping is explicit and stable.
